What is the appropriate bed or platform temperature for 3D printing using fused deposition modeling with polylactic acid (PLA) mixed with wood particles?
What is the appropriate nozzle diameter for 3D printing using fused deposition modeling with polylactic acid (PLA) mixed with wood particles?
messages.assistant_response:
The retrieved documents do not specify an exact recommended nozzle diameter for 3D printing with PLA mixed with wood particles. However, one document mentions that a 0.4 mm nozzle was used for printing test samples with wood-PLA filaments on a Zortrax M200 3D printer (reference_115.pdf, page 136). This suggests that a 0.4 mm nozzle is suitable for such material blends, at least in the context of the referenced study.

Reference: reference_115.pdf, page 136.
